Um...

45:24.492 --> 45:27.572
Primary repair worked.

45:32.852 --> 45:36.012
So, I guess the world
can look forward to, uh,

45:36.012 --> 45:42.092
a gaggle of olive-skinned kids
with red hair and freckles.

45:46.252 --> 45:48.572
If that's something
that you want.

45:58.012 --> 46:03.332
The life you lead, the things
you have been through...

46:03.332 --> 46:05.812
They define how you do your job,

46:05.932 --> 46:07.492
the quality of...

46:07.612 --> 46:10.292
the quality of your work.

46:10.412 --> 46:12.132
Especially in a place like this.

46:12.292 --> 46:15.372
So at the, um...

46:15.532 --> 46:17.972
At the end of the day,
you choose to...

46:18.092 --> 46:20.332
deny or deal.

46:25.092 --> 46:27.092
And which do you choose?

46:32.051 --> 46:35.211
It's evolving.

46:35.211 --> 46:37.531
I'm evolving.

46:37.531 --> 46:38.811
Um...

46:42.691 --> 46:46.771
All I know is that I know...

46:46.771 --> 46:51.651
um, that there is a lot of work
that I need to do.

46:53.091 --> 46:56.651
Can you be more specific
about that?

46:58.491 --> 47:02.411
No. Not with you.

47:09.091 --> 47:11.211
Mrs Taggart?

47:13.211 --> 47:14.491
Hi.

47:14.491 --> 47:17.371
Tony Gates. I work with Sam.

47:19.771 --> 47:21.811
I used to play.

47:21.811 --> 47:25.371
You know, Christmas time.
Play the carols.

47:25.371 --> 47:27.851
It's all gone now.

47:27.851 --> 47:31.091
Yeah. Well, Sam wanted me
to get this back to you.

47:31.091 --> 47:33.331
Well, she said
she was coming by.

47:33.451 --> 47:35.251
Well, she can't tonight.

47:35.331 --> 47:36.451
She's on a work call.

47:37.531 --> 47:38.571
Uh-huh.

47:38.691 --> 47:40.971
And you are?

47:41.091 --> 47:42.731
I am a friend.

47:42.851 --> 47:43.851
A friend?

47:45.331 --> 47:47.211
Do you smoke?

47:47.331 --> 47:49.451
No, ma'am, I don't.

47:49.571 --> 47:52.051
That's too bad.

47:52.051 --> 47:56.411
You're a good-looking fella,
though, aren't you?

47:56.531 --> 47:58.491
Hmm, must be the lighting in here.

47:59.971 --> 48:04.131
Do you know that out of
all these people in here,

48:04.291 --> 48:08.611
I'm the youngest one
by about 15 years?

48:08.611 --> 48:12.370
What the hell did I do
to deserve this?

48:14.650 --> 48:16.930
I can't imagine.

48:25.890 --> 48:28.810
I don't want her
to stop coming.

48:28.810 --> 48:32.650
So, if she thinks that's so,
you tell her it's not.

48:32.650 --> 48:34.370
OK.

48:34.370 --> 48:40.330
You know,
Sam's an amazing person.
She's very strong.

48:40.330 --> 48:43.610
She's overcome
a lot of obstacles.

48:43.610 --> 48:45.730
You get to know her,
you'd be very proud.

48:45.730 --> 48:48.490
She hates me.

48:48.490 --> 48:51.010
No, she doesn't.
Well, she thinks
that I hate her.

48:51.010 --> 48:52.210
Well, then, change that.

48:54.170 --> 48:55.730
Sure.

48:55.730 --> 48:57.650
Ta-dah!

48:57.650 --> 48:59.770
Changed!

48:59.770 --> 49:03.210
Well... It's up to you.

49:04.810 --> 49:06.570
Have a good night.

49:09.170 --> 49:10.330
Hey.

49:10.330 --> 49:13.090
You're not lying, are you?

49:13.090 --> 49:15.530
She's going
to come back tomorrow?

49:15.530 --> 49:19.090
When Sam makes up her mind,
nothing stops her.

49:32.450 --> 49:34.050
I love helping people.

49:34.290 --> 49:36.770
You know, originally,
i wanted to, um,

49:36.930 --> 49:39.530
be the first baseman
for the Chicago Cubs.

49:39.650 --> 49:40.810
The thing I hate most
about my job?

49:40.890 --> 49:41.970
Mm-hm.

49:42.130 --> 49:44.130
- Smells.
- The smells.

49:44.130 --> 49:46.450
The human body's got
some pretty interesting smells.

49:46.850 --> 49:49.250
What's-what's
the dating life like?

49:49.250 --> 49:51.609
Well, I'm not going to tell you.

49:52.009 --> 49:53.689
It's personal.

49:54.689 --> 49:56.889
A patient is a patient.

49:57.049 --> 50:00.129
Um...pain is pain.
It's-it's universal.

50:00.289 --> 50:03.049
I reached a point
about five years ago

50:03.169 --> 50:06.329
where I started to feel

50:06.489 --> 50:10.969
that every day was the same thing,
and I'd had enough.

50:10.969 --> 50:15.409
But I've been through
a lot of stuff since then.

50:18.929 --> 50:22.969
And now,
I try to embrace the idea

50:22.969 --> 50:27.769
that everything that happens
has never happened before.

50:29.409 --> 50:35.369
Like that saying that you can't
stand in the same river twice

50:35.369 --> 50:40.569
because by the time
that you come back,
it's not the same river.

50:46.609 --> 50:48.649
And you're not the same man.

50:52.209 --> 50:53.929
Anyway...

50:55.969 --> 50:58.049
I look around this place now

50:58.049 --> 51:00.889
and I can't imagine
ever finding it boring.

51:02.249 --> 51:06.849
Cos right at the moment that
you think you've seen it all...

